<p><b>Peter F. Hamilton</b> (born 2 March 1960) is a <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">British</a> <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">author</a>. He is best known for writing <a href="/wiki/Space_opera" title="Space opera">space opera</a>. As of the publication of his tenth novel in 2004, his works had sold over two million copies worldwide, making him Britain's biggest-selling science fiction author<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>.</p>
